During a meeting between President Giammattei of Guatemala and Vice President Harris of the United States, both leaders expressed their commitment to working together on common goals. President Giammattei highlighted issues such as narcotrafficking, immigration, the fight against corruption, and the need to build prosperity in border areas. Vice President Harris emphasized the importance of the relationship between the two countries as neighbors and the interconnectedness of the world. She also discussed the shared interest in addressing migration and the need to create hope and trust among the people. Both leaders expressed their eagerness to collaborate and bring benefits to their respective countries.